Applications are implemented by reacting to specific events. Those events are, amongst others:
 The simulation has started: All static units (e.g. road side units) are set up (onStartup() is called) Once a vehicle has been added to the simulation, all its configured applications are initialized (onStartup() is called) The data of the vehicle has changed, e.g. after the traffic simulator has finished one simulationstep (onVehicleUpdated() is called). A unit has received a V2X message from another entity (onMessageReceived is called). A unit which has send a V2X message via a ITS-G5 topocast receives an acknowledgement (onAcknowledgementReceived() is called).  Another example:
